<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written Evidence from Healthwatch England [PHS0036]</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#4a4a49; font-family:'Museo 100'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Written Evidence from Healthwatch England [PHS0036]</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Healthwatch England welcomes the opportunity to provide written evidence to the Public Administration Committee on your inquiry into </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Complaints: do they make a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">difference</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. We hope that this provides a useful insight into the public’s concerns with the complaints systems and our proposed solutions for improvement and reform across health and social care.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Key messages:</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There is a catalogue of reports and inquirie</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s documenting problems with the complaints systems, but to date reform has been slow and resulted in limited improvement. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">People tell us that the complaints systems do not currently work and that they want a health and social care complaints system that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is: independent and confidential, responsive, supportive, simple, joined up and transparent.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We believe that the Healthwatch network can help to reform and improve complaints systems in health and social care by:</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.9pt; padding-left:3.1pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">increasing consumer awareness of their ri</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ght to raise concerns and how to make a complaint.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 69.44pt; padding-left:2.56pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ensuring high quality advocacy and support when people want to make a complaint or when things go wrong.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Many people do not know where to turn when they have a concern or complaint about a health or </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">social care service. There are multiple local and national complaints system, regulators and contact points, meaning the system is hard to navigate and few people are able to find a timely resolution for their complaint.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Our own research found that 3 in 5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of the public do not feel they have a clear way of providing feedback and at least half of the concerns they have are never reported, primarily because they did not have any confidence that their complaints would actually be dealt with.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">To address this, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Healthwatch England is committed to coordinating a consumer-facing complaints campaign to raise awareness about people’s rights to make complaints and the standards they should expect from complaints handling and advocacy services.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Similarly, we strongly </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">recommend an amendment to existing 2009 complaints regulations to enable ‘worried bystanders’ to raise concerns and would like to explore further the value that anonymised complaints could make to the improvement of local health and social care services.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The current complexity and inconsistency of local advocacy</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, Patient Advice and Liaison Services </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and support offers needs resolving.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We propose that the Department of Health work with Healthwatch England and advocacy organisations to e</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">stablish a new consol</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">idated complaints advocacy offer that spans health and social care across all settings.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Additionally, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">we propose that existing NHS Complaints Advocacy Services contracts</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> should</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> be kite-marked under the Healthwatch brand and required to collaborate with lo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">cal Healthwatch. </span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Context</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Concerns about the complaints systems for health and social care are not new. In 2000, the Ritchie inquiry published its findings which looked at why concerns about Rodney Ledward, over a 16 year period, were not dealt with </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">promptly to prevent his patients from being harmed</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. Ledward had faced numerous complaints from over 500 women and their families before being struck off by the GMC for serious professional misconduct in 1998.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The report recognised that many people did no</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">t know how to complain or to whom to complain to, and heard evidence that there was considerable dissatisfaction in the way complaints are dealt with both at local and national level. The inquiry found that the c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">omplaints procedure was so complicated that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">it would have probably acted as a deterrent to both staff and patients. It went on to state that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">complaints procedures were lengthy, cumbersome and time consuming and not in anyone's best interests. In their view the establishment of a simple and straightf</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">orward procedure for dealing with complaints would work to the benefit of patients and Trust employees (including doctors) alike. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Just four years later (in 2004), an independent inquiry</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> was underway into the murders of over 200 patients by their GP, Dr.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Harold Shipman over a period of more than 20 years. Significant concerns were raised about the complaints system. In its conclusions, the inquiry recommended a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> single portal by which complaints or concerns could be directed or redirected to the appropriat</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e quarter, incorporating a single national telephone number and internet service.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Worryingly, concerns about the inadequacy of complaints processes were highlighted in the serious failings at Mid Staffordshire NHS Foundation Trust between 2005 and 2009. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Sir Robert Francis QC, who led two public inquiries</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> into the failings, found that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Trust management and governance lacked a culture of listening to patients and there were inadequate processes for dealing with complaints or supporting people to raise conce</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">rns that they had about their treatment or care. The second inquiry went on to suggest that a uniform process of complaints handling should be applied, and the making of a complaint should be easy to do with the facilitation of a speedy resolution, whereve</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">r possible.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Further reports this year (2013) from Professor Sir Bruce Keogh</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, Professor Don Berwick</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and the Clwyd /Hart review</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, commissioned by the Prime Minister, recognised that there has </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">been a systematic failure to listen to, and act upon, the conce</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">rns of patients, carers and families and these failures resulted in neglect, poor quality care and even death.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Healthwatch England is concerned by the lack of progress made on improving and reforming complaints systems in health and social care, and we be</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lieve that action must be taken now to prevent another crisis. To this end, Healthwatch England has prioritised work on complaints reform</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and we welcome the opportunity to give evidence to the committee about our concerns with the current system and propo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sals for reform.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Our proposals for improvement and reform are based on own work on complaints and reviewing of previous proposals and actions made by independent inquiries.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Principles for reform</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In June 2013, Healthwatch England launched a video report</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">exploring the public’s experience of health and social care complaints systems. Our work with consumers and sector leaders enabled us to identify six core principles for complaint reform. People told us that they wanted a system of complaints handling and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">advocacy that was: </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Independent and confidential:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> a service that they could trust to look at things impartially, that raising a concern does not adversely affect their treatment or care and that respects their privacy and progresses their concern or complaint to a satisfactory resolution.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Responsive:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">service that listens to the needs, preferences and anxieties of the people making complaints and responds to them in a timely manner, in a way that works for them. </span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Supportive:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> a service that helps and supports them to navigate through any complex or diff</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">icult stages in making a complaint. </span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Simple:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> a system that is easy to understand whereby people know what their rights are and what they should expect from complaints handling and advocacy services.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Joined up: </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">a system where people only have to raise a c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">oncern or make a complaint once, where any door is the right door and any complexity of case handling (like coordinating multiple complaints to a provider, professional body and regulator) all happen behind the scenes, rather than the person having to navi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">gate this themselves. This would be accompanied by one complaints advocacy offer so you know who is supporting you from the start to the resolution of your case.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Transparent:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> a system that is up-front about the processes that are being used and the decisi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ons that are being made, keeping people up to date with any changes in their case.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Consumer rights and complaints reform</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We have been working with the public to develop a new framework of consumer rights for health and social care</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. The eight rights</span><a name="_ftnref10"></a><a href="#_ftn10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> we have developed are based on the international guidelines adopted by the United Nations in 1985, and expanded in 1999.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We took these eight international consumer rights and tested them with representatives from local Healthwatch and the public, drawing</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> on their own experiences of the health and social care system. People helped us to develop the rights at a deliberative workshop, reflections after the event that we captured on video and through nearly two thousand interviews during the summer of 2013. W</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e also spoke to academics and researchers about the rights and explored different international and domestic models to make sure we hadn’t missed anything.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The complete set of rights is listed below. In relation to complaints specifically, the public focu</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sed on a right to be listened to and provided us with many examples of where the complaints system and advocacy had let them down.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to essential services:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Everyone has the right to a set of basic and essential treatment and care services at a defined standard.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to access:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> I have the right to access services on an equal basis with others, when I need them and in a way that works for me and my famil</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">y.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to a safe, dignified and quality service:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> I have the right to high quality, safe services that treat me with dignity, compassion and respect.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to information and education: </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">I have the right to information and education about how to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">take care of myself and what I am entitled to within the health and social care system.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to choose:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> I have the right to choose from a range of high quality services, products and providers within health and social care.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to be listened </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">to:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> I have the right to have my concerns and views listened to and acted upon. I have the right to be supported in taking action if I am not satisfied with the service I have received.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to be involved:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> I am an equal partner in determining my own </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">health and wellbeing. I have the right to be involved in decisions that affect my life and those affecting services in my local community.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.48pt; padding-left:2.52pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The right to live in a healthy environment:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> I have the right to live in an environment that promotes positive health</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and wellbeing.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Based on these consumer rights, and the public’s principles for reform, we propose three roles that the Healthwatch network could take on to increase independence, accountability and effectiveness in the health and social care complaints s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ystem. We believe there is a role for Healthwatch in:</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.23pt; padding-left:11.22pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">raising consumer awareness of their right to raise concerns and how to make a complaint.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24.23pt; padding-left:11.22pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ensuring high quality advocacy and support when people want to make a complaint or when things go wrong.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.9pt; padding-left:3.1pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Raising consumer awareness and ease of access.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Consumers do not know where to turn when they have a concern or complaint about a health or social care service. There are multiple local and national complaints system, regulators and contact points, meaning</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> the system is hard to navigate and few people are able to find a timely resolution for their complaint.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Our own research found that 3 in 5 of the public do not feel they have a clear way of providing feedback and at least half of the concerns they have a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">re never reported, primarily because they did not have any confidence that their complaints would actually be dealt with</span><a name="_ftnref11"></a><a href="#_ftn11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. People shared with us experiences that resulted in a substantive lack of trust and confidence in complaints handling and concerns of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">independence and sufficiency of resolution processes. This means that many instances of poor care and treatment are not registered and could mean poor practice unnecessarily escalates.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Similarly, we are concerned that the current 2009 complaint regulation</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><a name="_ftnref12"></a><a href="#_ftn12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> effectively prevent ‘worried bystanders’ from registering any concerns or complaints they have about a health or care service. We strongly recommend an amendment to existing regulations to enable ‘worried bystanders’ to raise concerns and would like to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">explore further the value that anonymised complaints could make to the improvement of local health and social care services.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We are supportive of the ideas, promoted by Parliamentary &amp; Health Services Ombudsman (PHSO), for consumers to have a single point</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of contact during their journey through the complaints system – and we are aware of the possibility that NHS England will develop this. The scale of this service would not be appropriate for Healthwatch to deliver and it potentially threatens the value we</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> could offer in independent oversight, scrutiny and support of the complaints system. However, we would want to ensure that any such system would meet the needs of consumers and fits with the existing or future role Healthwatch could play in the complaints</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> landscape.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We feel it should be the role of Healthwatch to support consumers to navigate the system and to support them to understand what to expect when they raise a concern or complaint. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Based on the recommendations of the recent Clwyd Hart review</span><a name="_ftnref13"></a><a href="#_ftn13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> into NHS hospitals complaints systems, Healthwatch England is committed to coordinating a consumer-facing complaints campaign to raise awareness about people’s rights to make complaints and the standards they should expect from complaints handling and adv</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ocacy services. To support this we are keen to collaborate with the Department of Health, the PHSO, the Local Government Ombudsman (LGO) and others to develop and promote a complaints supplement to the NHS Constitution</span><a name="_ftnref14"></a><a href="#_ftn14">[14]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, which explicitly articulates the st</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">andards that consumers should expect from local and national complaints handling services.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In addition to this, we are supporting local Healthwatch to undertake pilot work to improve local complaints systems in low performing commissioner or provider area</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s and to develop good practice in specified communities (i.e. for people with mental health conditions or living in areas of multiple deprivation). We believe that this will result in co-designed practical solutions to improve local complaint systems and e</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">nable Healthwatch England to share this with the wider network to be replicated in other areas.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.44pt; padding-left:2.56pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Ensuring high quality advocacy and support for those wanting to raise a concern or resolve a complaint.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Advocacy is support for people who are making a compla</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">int – from assistance with letter writing through to help navigating a complex system and representation in meetings that may be confusing or distressing for individuals. This service is particularly important when a complaint spans more than one resolutio</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">n process (local, courts, fitness to practice) and because many people feel vulnerable or exposed at the time of making a complaint about their care or treatment.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Complaints advocacy in the NHS is far more developed than in social care. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Initially, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Community Health Councils (established in 1974</span><a name="_ftnref15"></a><a href="#_ftn15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">) had a remit to give</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> advice and support to members of the public on how to go about making a complaint about their local health services, until they were abolished in 2003</span><a name="_ftnref16"></a><a href="#_ftn16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Currently support is offered thro</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ugh NHS Complaints Advocacy Services (NHS CAS)</span><a name="_ftnref17"></a><a href="#_ftn17">[17]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, which replaced the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Independent Complaints Advocacy Service (ICAS) for the NHS that operated from September 2003 to April 2013. Whereas NHS CAS are commissioned by local authorities, ICAS were commissioned on</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> a regional basis to provide </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">support for people wishing to complain about their treatment or care received under the NHS</span><a name="_ftnref18"></a><a href="#_ftn18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. The total </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">indicative budget for the commissioning of NHS CAS was £14.2m</span><a name="_ftnref19"></a><a href="#_ftn19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, which includes an additional settlement to cover the lost e</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">conomies of scale that were achieved under ICAS. Whilst NHS CAS is primarily commissioned to focus on health complaints, in some areas (based of commissioner appetite or provider passion) support is also offered to those who have a social care complaint.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The current complexity and inconsistency of local advocacy and support offers need resolving. There are concerns the sufficiency and coverage of local NHS CAS and the extent to which they are supporting individuals to find local resolutions to their concer</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ns or complaints. In some areas NHS CAS have been commissioned to the same organisation that runs the local Healthwatch. In these areas we are starting to see a more consolidated complaints advocacy and support offer. However, there is now an inconsistency</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in access to complaints advocacy across local areas reliant on the appetite of councils and availability of resource. </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Coverage for social care complaints advocacy is under significant threat as there is no overall duty on councils to provide independent</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> support to those raising a concern or making a complaint. Increasingly, councils are cutting the discretionary advocacy they commission as local budgets come under significant pressure.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Additionally, we are hearing concerns about the independence and poo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">r / inconsistent standards of service among Patient Advice and Liaison Services (PALs) and inadequate signposting and collaboration with local NHS CAS and local Healthwatch. PALS were created in 2002 to provide information and on the spot help where patien</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ts want to resolve a problem without making a formal complaint. Its role was to provide confidential advice, support and reassurance, and to resolve small problems locally. </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">PALS should be resourced to ensure staff are fully aware of the complaints proced</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ure and trained to recognise and address complaints by either providing information on the complaints procedure or referring the complainant to the local NHS CAS. Whilst the Health and Social Care Act</span><a name="_ftnref20"></a><a href="#_ftn20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> abolished commissioner (Primary Care Trust) PALS, prov</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ider (hospital) PALS remain in place.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">To end the current inconsistency in the system, we propose the Government establish a new consolidated complaints advocacy offer that spans health and social care, and all settings. Healthwatch England are keen to wor</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">k with the Department of Health, and advocacy providers to design and promote new standards for this consolidated complaints advocacy offer.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Further, we propose that existing NHS CAS contracts be kite-marked under the Healthwatch brand and required to col</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">laborate with local Healthwatch. This would simplify entry in the system for consumers as well as ensuring oversight of the quality of the advocacy offer. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Once existing contracts for NHS CAS and / or local Healthwatch have been fulfilled, we believe there </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is an opportunity for the Government to reconsider how a consolidated advocacy and support offer might be commissioned.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">We believe that these solutions should enable Healthwatch England to develop a source of national data on local health and social care </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">complaints, which is currently not held at a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">national level, allowing us to identify national trends and concerns that need to be acted upon.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Finally, we note that Rt Hon. Oliver Letwin (Minister for Government Policy), in his evidence to your committee, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">announced further reviews into complaints systems, which includes the NHS. We would also hope that Healthwatch England are offered the opportunity to champion consumer interest in such a review and ensure that learning from new efforts to improve and refor</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">m the health and social complaints systems is adequately captured.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p s